The paper involves using deep reinforcement learning to train an automated vehicle to negotiate with other vehicles in intersections. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) as it involves training an agent to make decisions in a dynamic environment. The use of deep learning also suggests that it could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) as these are common techniques used in deep learning. Finally, the paper involves the interaction between multiple vehicles, which suggests it could also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
